The paper discusses evolutionary multitasking, which involves solving multiple optimization tasks simultaneously using a unified solution representation scheme. This topic is closely related to machine learning and optimization, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category, as it explicitly mentions evolutionary computation. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories, as they cover topics related to optimization and multitasking. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category, as it covers optimization algorithms. Finally, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely category, but it could be relevant if the paper discusses software implementation or engineering aspects of evolutionary multitasking.
